==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Woods metal
<hw>Wood's" met"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A fusible alloy consisting of
one or two parts of cadmium, two parts of tin, four of lead, with seven
or eight part of bismuth. It melts at from 66⟦deg⟧ to 71⟦deg⟧ C. See
<cref>Fusible metal</cref>, under <er>Fusible</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woodstone</ent>⟦br⟧
